Some History: Smith & Wesson had been purchased by a conglomerate named Bangor Punta. In 1970, Bangor Punta also purchased 54% of Taurus. Thus, the two companies became "sisters". What may come as a surprise to some is that more of what was "right" in Porto Alegre was sent to Springfield than was sent from Springfield to south of the equator.

title: For Sale:  J. Stevens Arms & Tool Company Model 425 35cal
postcontent:
The Model 425 High Power represented the J. Stevens Arms & Tool Company's entry into the center fire lever arena. Although some sources claim that there were 26,000 of these guns made, it is more likely that only about 5,000 were made. It was produced (or at least cataloged) from 1911 through 1917 and serialized with at least one other Stevens gun during that period (which accounts for the high production number). It is a unique design, capturing the best features of its competitors guns (Winchester and Marlin) at the time. It was tapped on the top of the receiver for a scope or target sight, ejects to the right and is very esthetically pleasing with its 22" barrel and 2/3 magazine. Apparently sales did not go well which accounts for the relative scarcity of these rifles. 

This gun is in excellent condition for its age. It is chambered for the 35 Remington cartridge. The metal is in exceptional condition with the bluing better than 85% remaining on the receiver and barrel. The magazine tube and forend cap show thinning blue as does the bottom of the receiver from carrying. Overall, the gun is in great condition for its age. There is no box or original paperwork with this gun.

title: For Sale:  Bersa Thunder 380 CC $300 O.B.O.
postcontent:
.380 acp semi-automatic pistol. Great starter pistol or for Concealed Carry. I have bought a different CC pistol and no longer need this one. This pistol is in great shape and has already been warranty repaired by Colorado Gun Works. These pistols have a factory problem of a spring jumping out the notch that is suppose to ride in and then fires erractically. CGW has machined the notch a little deeper and then inserted the spring and staked it off. Unlike a lot of other Bersa's out there, this one will now fire reliably when needed. Great pistol, just not needed anymore. Comes is factory box, key for integrated trigger lock, external trigger lock, factory test round, blackhawk holster, and factory magazine. One of the coolest features of this pistol is that fact that it is a Double Action/Single Action pistol with a De-cocker. This means you can breach a bullet into the chamber and then de-cock it. So then if you needed to defend yourself it will take a harder, safer, double action trigger pull to get the first round off. Then every round after that is single action. Love this feature. Alot of your smaller CC pistol are Double Action only, of which is not nearly as accurate as sngle action. Email if you would like to set up a meet to look at this pistol.

Price is $300 O.B.O.

title: For Sale:  AK-74
postcontent:
I have a Polish AK-74 in 5.45X39 cal in excellent condition. This is the caliber the Russians switched to in 1974.  They found it vastly superior to the the 7.62X39, they used to use.  (They never switched back).  

   This caliber extends the effective range by several hundred meters.  It has high velocity, much flatter trajectory, better accuracy, longer range, and almost NO recoil.  It has a reputation as a much better "stopper".  Afgan fighters feared it, and called it the "Poison bullet".

   Ammo is the cheapest center fire you can by.  (1080 rds in sealed cans for $139.)

   Rifle comes with a side folding, military issue, metal butt stock. (It can be fired with stock folded.)  Tapco trigger is EXCELLENT!  This is the only model that has safety access on BOTH sides of receiver.  You can take off safety with hand still on pistol grip.  Forearm has high quality rails on top, both sides, and bottom.   Red dot, laser, light and vertical grip/bipod can be easily mounted.  Two 30 rd mags included.

   This is the one you want when it all hits the fan!!!
